In a speech at the Hudson Institute in Washington, D.C., Vice President Mike Pence accused China of attempting to undermine the Trump administration and interfere in American politics. He accused Beijing of using political, economic, military, and propaganda tools to advance its influence and benefit its interests in the United States. Pence criticized China's trade practices, intellectual property theft, forced technology transfer, military expansion, human rights abuses, and censorship. He also highlighted China's efforts to influence American public opinion and the upcoming midterm elections. Pence vowed that the United States will continue to defend its interests and demand fair and reciprocal trade with China.